<TITLE> Govt suppressing opposition with false cases: Khaleda </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 22 (bdnews24.com) - BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia said Thursday that the government was filing false cases against leaders and workers of the opposition party to deter them from mounting any opposition to against its failures. "Failures cannot be concealed by such oppression and harassment cases," the leader of the opposition said as just-released BNP leader Amanullah Aman met with Khaleda at her political office in Gulshan. Earlier that evening, Aman was freed from prison guard at his cabin at Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University. A Dhaka court had granted the former state minister bail in a case that implicates him in an armed attack to kill businessman Osman Gani. "This government has turned into a failed government," said Khaleda. "The government has not been able to implement its election pledges. The people want to be rid of this government," she said. Khaleda also said her party leaders and workers must stand united to make strengthen BNP. Barrister Rafiqul Haque, senior party leaders Khandaker Mosharraf Hossain, Abdul Moeen Khan and former speaker Jamiruddin Sircar also met with Khaleda on Thursday. b
